 Zipporah Kittony has advised farmers to shift from maize farming to coffee and tea. Mrs Kittony, a former senator, said maize farming had impoverished many families in the region due to poor prices and delays in payments. ALSO READ:

Governor Kiraitu defends himself from claims of using miraa funds “Maize has become a frustrating venture. We can only tame poverty if we diversify,” she said in Kitale yesterday.